The paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a problem in computer vision, hence it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a generative adversarial network based model, which involves deep learning techniques, making it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves affine transformations, which are commonly used in computer graphics (cs.GR) and the paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a problem in multimodal learning (cs.MM).
